This paper deals with training Convolutional Networks for image classification, which falls under the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of noise layers and modifications to the training process, which are relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing experiments, which could place it under the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image datasets, which could also place it under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
